Consider the parametric curve:

$\begin{align}
x&=\dfrac{-5}{t^2}
\\\\
y&=e^{-t}
\end{align}$

**Which integral gives the arc length of the curve over the interval from $t=-5$ to $t=0$?**

[[☃ radio 1]]

hints:
Let's find $\dfrac{dx}{dt}$ and $\dfrac{dy}{dt}$:

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{dx}{dt}&=\dfrac{d}{dt}\left[\dfrac{-5}{t^2}\right]
\\\\
&=\dfrac{10}{t^3}
\\\\\\
\dfrac{dy}{dt}&=\dfrac{d}{dt}\left[e^{-t}\right]
\\\\
&=-e^{-t}
\end{align}$

